comments: Collins (ATL) jumps towards Ingram (NOP) and marginal contact occurs as they both pursue the loose ball.
Jones (NOP) moves alongside of Young (ATL) and marginal body contact occurs while defending his driving shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (NOP) and Murray (ATL) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
After Capela (ATL) gathers the loose ball, Nance Jr. (NOP) lightly brushes his arm and makes incidental contact to Capela's lower body after the release of his pass attempt.
Ingram (NOP) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Murray's (ATL) body after the release.
Nance Jr (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position and is firming up when contact occurs.
Ingram (NOP) establishes himself in Young's (ATL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Nance Jr. (NOP) briefly grasps Collins' (ATL) arm after the hand off and immediately disengages as they move towards the rim.
Capela (ATL) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in Jones' (NOP) path and marginal shoulder contact occurs as they separate.
After Collins (ATL) secures the loose ball, Nance Jr. (NOP) swipes down and initiates contact to his wrist that affects his ability to maintain control of the ball.
McCollum (NOP) and Hunter (ATL) mutually engage and disengage with one another as they pursue the loose ball.
McCollum (NOP) is the last person to touch the ball. The possession is correctly awarded to ATL.
Jones (NOP) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Young (ATL) after the release.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hunter (ATL) grasps and then quickly releases Nance Jr.'s (NOP) jersey as he gathers the pass.
Jones (NOP) places his forearm on Young's (ATL) body and marginal contact body occurs off-ball as they disengage.
Capela (ATL) legally contests Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
McCollum (NOP) is moving alongside Murray's (ATL) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Capela (ATL) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Williamson (NOP) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Hunter (ATL) and incidental contact occurs as Hunter (ATL) attempts to move over the screen.
Hunter (ATL) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Ingram's (NOP) arm after the release.
Collins' (ATL) left hand grabs Williamson's (NOP) wrist, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Capela (ATL) jumps vertically and absorbs the body contact from Williamson (NOP) at the end of the drive.
Williamson (NOP) briefly grasps Collins' (ATL) arm off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Williamson (NOP) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Jones (NOP) jumps somewhat towards Capela (ATL) and marginal contact occurs to Capela's (ATL) extended leg as he attempts to pass.
Capela (ATL) places a resting hand on Ingram (NOP), which he retracts as he jumps alongside Ingram's path during the driving shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) and McCollum (NOP) mutually engage and disengage with one another as they pursue the long rebound.

Young (ATL) wraps his arm around McCollum's (NOP) side and initiates contact after his gather, affecting his driving shot attempt. Although the call is correct, continuation should have been awarded due to the contact occurring after McCollum's gather.
Capela (ATL) extends both hands to McCollum's (NOP) upper body after his gather.
Ingram (NOP) jumps somewhat toward Young (ATL) and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hunter (ATL) grasps and then quickly releases Nance Jr.'s (NOP) jersey off-ball.
Capela (ATL) briefly places his hands against Ingram's (NOP) body and quickly releases defending his drive to the basket.
Hunter (ATL) briefly engages with Nance Jr. (NOP) off-ball before separating during Ingram's (NOP) driving shot attempt.
Jones (NOP) briefly grasps Hunter's (ATL) leg and quickly releases as he defends over the pick.
Ingram (NOP) hedges the pick and marginal contact occurs as he briefly places and retracts his hands from Young (ATL) during the drive.
Murray (ATL) briefly places his hands to Ingram's (NOP) front and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the screen.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Murray's (ATL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Nance Jr. (NOP) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Hunter (ATL) and incidental contact occurs as Hunter attempts to move over the screen.
Capela (ATL) initiates body contact with Nance Jr. (NOP) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Jones (NOP) immediately slides his hand off of Young's (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Nance Jr. (NOP) commits a take foul on Capela (ATL).
Ingram (NOP) and Hunter (ATL) engage and disengage with one another prior to the inbound pass.
Collins (ATL) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Ingram (NOP) and incidental contact occurs as Ingram (NOP) attempts to move over the screen.
Graham (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Murray (ATL) prior to any incidental contact occurring thereafter on the shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (NOP) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path as he sets the pick and absorbs the contact.
Collins (ATL) closes out on McCollum (NOP) and marginal body contact occurs after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Murray (ATL) moves laterally into Jones' (NOP) body as he is airborne on his put-back shot attempt.
Jones (NOP) cleanly deflects the inbound pass prior to any incidental contact occurring with Young (ATL).
Holiday (ATL) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from Ingram (NOP) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Nance Jr. (NOP) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and absorbs the body contact from Hunter (ATL) during the screen.
Graham (NOP) steps out of bounds as he gathers the pass and prior to any contact occuring during his jump shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (NOP) places a resting forearm on Collins' (ATL) body and he is able to move through the marginal contact to gather the pass.
